name: Royce Lake Falls
description:
Approach

COMPLETED AS A TWO DAY TRIP. AN 8 MILE HIKE UP TO PiNE CREEK PASS AT 11,200' AND SET CAMP. COMPLETED CANYON NEXT DAY AND ASCENDED BACK UP TO CAMP, AND THEN BACK OUT TO CAR

Descent

First waterfall cascade approximately 450 / 500', but broken into different rappels - some out of the water course. Warmer water the falls should be done in the water, and not outside of it. Lower Falls aprox. 300 / 350' and done like the upper falls

Exit

Red tape
